$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Gallwch ddefnyddio hecsadegol i drosi rhwng gwerthoedd degol a deuaidd. Er enghraifft, byddai trosi 10011011001010 yn hecsadegol yn arwain at 0x4F. Mae hyn yn golygu bod y gwerth 4F yn cynrychioli&#39;r rhif deuaidd 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Mewn mathemateg a chyfrifiadureg, mae hecsadegol (hefyd sylfaen 16, neu hecs) yn system rifol safle gyda radix, neu sylfaen, o 16. Mae&#39;n defnyddio un ar bymtheg o symbolau gwahanol, gan amlaf y symbolau 0–9 i gynrychioli gwerthoedd sero i naw, ac A, B, C, D, E, F (neu a–f) i gynrychioli gwerthoedd o ddeg i bymtheg. Er enghraifft, mae’r rhif hecsadegol 2AF3 yn hafal, mewn degol, i (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160), neu 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Mae pob digid hecsadegol yn cynrychioli pedwar digid deuaidd (didiau) (a elwir hefyd yn &quot;dennyn&quot;), a&#39;r prif ddefnydd o nodiant hecsadegol yw fel cynrychiolaeth ddynol-gyfeillgar o werthoedd cod deuaidd mewn cyfrifiadureg ac electroneg ddigidol. Er enghraifft, gall gwerthoedd beit amrywio o 0 i 255 (degol) ond gallant gael eu cynrychioli&#39;n fwy cyfleus fel dau ddigid hecsadegol yn yr ystod 00 i FF. Mae hecsadegol hefyd yn cael ei ddefnyddio&#39;n gyffredin i gynrychioli cyfeiriadau cof cyfrifiadurol.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Talfyriad o Hecsadegol yw Hex, sy&#39;n seiliedig ar strwythur sylfaen -16 ac a ddefnyddir i symleiddio sut mae cyfarwyddiadau i gyfrifiaduron yn cael eu cynrychioli. Datblygwyd y system rhif 16 symbol hwn fel modd o atal rhif deuaidd 8-did, fel y gellir amgodio data i gyfrifiaduron yn ddiymdrech. Gellir ei argraffu a&#39;i deipio gan ddefnyddio dau ddigid hecs gwahanol gyda phob digid hecs yn dangos fformat brith neu efallai 4-did.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Mae&#39;r system rif hon yn defnyddio 16 symbol sy&#39;n cael eu cynrychioli mewn ystod o 0-9 neu AF. Mae&#39;r 0–9 yn cynrychioli rhifau hyd at naw tra bod AF yn cael ei gynrychioli gan y rhifol 10–15. O gymharu â&#39;r tri math arall o systemau rhif, ystyrir mai&#39;r system rhifiadol hecsadegol yw&#39;r un mwyaf effeithiol.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Mae eich cod hecsadegol yn annilys';
